      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span clinically relevant range of loading rates and environmental conditions; at minimum two distinct test conditions evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. Physiological loading rates and in vivo temperature not replicated. Single test condition falls below Gradation 3 requirement. This factor is identified as below required level; residual uncertainty acknowledged in overall credibility assessment. Gradation 2 achieved."
