      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical risk (construct stiffness governs load sharing with bone; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement govern fatigue life and failure risk); linkage documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly linked to clinical performance: stiffness governs load transfer to the fusion mass; yield force and post-yield behavior govern fatigue crack initiation risk. Clinical relevance documented in risk analysis. Gradation 3 achieved."
